{{unref|date=October 2008}} In [[operations research]] and [[engineering]], a '''criticality matrix''' is a representation (often graphical) of [[failure mode]]s along with their [[probability|probabilities]] and severities.
==Example==
For example, an aircraft might have the following matrix:
{| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! Failure mode ! Severity ! Probability |- | Collision | High | Low |- | Engine failure | High | Low |- | Ice buildup | Medium | High |}
[[Category:Industrial engineering]]
